# Project Builder Build Shortcut

When the user says `build` while working in `flux-2-swift-mix`, read:

`~/GitHub/utility-be-project-builder/Configs/flux-2-swift-mix.json`

Then run the Project Builder workflow from that config:

- Honor `run_preferences` when present, clamped by `capabilities`.
- If `run_preferences` is absent, default to compile only.
- Execute `commands.compile`, `commands.relocate`, and `commands.launch` from the repo root only when enabled.
- For relocate, skip and report if `overwrite` is false and `relocate.destination` already exists.

If the user says `compile`, do a normal compile only and do not use Project Builder.
